WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.172 --> 00:00:08.299
Hi. I'm Dylan Minnette.
and I play Clay Jensen.

2
00:00:08.466 --> 00:00:10.677
I'm Katherine Langford.
and I play Hannah Baker.

3
00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:12.929
I'm Justin Prentice. I play Bryce Walker.

4
00:00:13.012 --> 00:00:15.432
I'm Alisha Boe. I play Jessica Davis.

5
00:00:15.598 --> 00:00:18.018
13 Reasons Why is a fictional series

6
00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:20.478
that tackles tough. real-world issues.

7
00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:22.772
taking a look at sexual assault.

8
00:00:22.939 --> 00:00:25.650
substance abuse. suicide. and more.

9
00:00:25.734 --> 00:00:27.902
By shedding a light
on these difficult topics.

10
00:00:27.986 --> 00:00:30.655
we hope our show can help viewers
start a conversation.

11
00:00:30.739 --> 00:00:33.533
But if you are struggling
with these issues yourself.

12
00:00:33.783 --> 00:00:35.452
this series may not be right for you.

13
00:00:35.618 --> 00:00:37.787
or you may want to watch it
with a trusted adult.

14
00:00:37.871 --> 00:00:40.123
And if you ever feel you need someone
to talk with.

15
00:00:40.206 --> 00:00:41.833
reach out to a parent. a friend.

16
00:00:41.916 --> 00:00:44.377
a school counselor. or an adult you trust.

17
00:00:44.461 --> 00:00:47.547
call a local helpline.
or go to 13ReasonsWhy.info.

18
00:00:47.630 --> 00:00:49.924
Because the minute you start
talking about it.

19
00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:51.760
it gets easier.

20
00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:22.207
Good morning. ladies and gentlemen.

21
00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:24.959
Calling the case
of Andrew and Olivia Baker

22
00:01:25.043 --> 00:01:27.545
versus the Evergreen County
School District.

23
00:01:28.379 --> 00:01:30.298
Are both sides ready to begin?

24
00:01:35.053 --> 00:01:36.471
She was so beautiful.

25
00:01:38.306 --> 00:01:41.142
And she was so nice to me.

26
00:01:41.893 --> 00:01:46.189
Tyler. you testified that life
at Liberty High School was bad

27
00:01:46.272 --> 00:01:48.024
before Hannah Baker killed herself.

28
00:01:48.108 --> 00:01:48.983
How is it now?

29
00:01:52.028 --> 00:01:52.862
Tyler?

30
00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:56.407
It's worse.

31
00:02:06.918 --> 00:02:07.919
Hey! Watch it!

32
00:02:10.046 --> 00:02:11.256
- Whoa!
- Hey!

33
00:02:11.339 --> 00:02:14.175
It's been five months
since Hannah Baker killed herself.

34
00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:16.803
We never thought this trial would happen.

35
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:19.347
We thought we could move on.

36
00:02:20.974 --> 00:02:25.478
But when I got called to testify.
it made me realize we can't just move on.

37
00:02:26.187 --> 00:02:32.777
♪ Oh. I've just come
From the land of the sun ♪

38
00:02:32.861 --> 00:02:33.987
Life is different now.

39
00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:38.950
♪ From a war that must be won
In the name of truth ♪

40
00:02:39.826 --> 00:02:43.705
♪ With our soldiers so brave ♪

41
00:02:43.788 --> 00:02:47.125
What did we say about red lights?
You promised me.

42
00:02:47.542 --> 00:02:49.752
I promise you a lot of things.

43
00:02:50.420 --> 00:02:51.379
You got your ID?

44
00:02:55.466 --> 00:02:57.302
"Cody Jantzen" from Texas.

45
00:02:57.844 --> 00:02:58.928
And are you ready for this?

46
00:03:00.805 --> 00:03:02.307
I am. I'm ready.

47
00:03:02.891 --> 00:03:05.852
It's like you said. it'll help me
put that part of my life to rest.

48
00:03:05.935 --> 00:03:08.229
-It shows I found closure--
-Yeah. Totally.

49
00:03:08.313 --> 00:03:11.441
But I meant. are you ready for the needle?

50
00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:15.862
Breathe deep. Stay calm.

51
00:03:17.822 --> 00:03:19.032
I'm good. I'm fine.

52
00:03:20.199 --> 00:03:21.618
It's his first time.

53
00:03:23.036 --> 00:03:23.870
Really?

54
00:03:25.288 --> 00:03:28.708
So. the semi-colon.
it's for a friend of yours?

55
00:03:30.251 --> 00:03:31.085
Yeah. Yeah.

56
00:03:32.128 --> 00:03:32.962
I'm sorry.

57
00:03:34.672 --> 00:03:35.506
Thanks.

58
00:03:38.426 --> 00:03:39.260
Half done.

59
00:03:43.181 --> 00:03:44.015
Wow.

60
00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:47.936
Sweet. All right. cool.

61
00:03:49.103 --> 00:03:50.104
Yeah. keep going.

62
00:03:54.442 --> 00:03:56.903
The truth is.
everyone's still hurting.

63
00:03:58.696 --> 00:04:00.198
Some more than others.

64
00:04:04.035 --> 00:04:05.370
Oh. shit.

65
00:04:07.497 --> 00:04:08.957
It's a fucking comma.

66
00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:11.709
So it signifies a pause.

67
00:04:12.835 --> 00:04:15.964
As in. you paused getting a tattoo
in order to faint.

68
00:04:17.131 --> 00:04:19.550
Even just getting the tattoo.
I fucking fail.

69
00:04:22.178 --> 00:04:23.096
Hey.

70
00:04:24.555 --> 00:04:26.015
Hannah will forgive you.

71
00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:32.814
Look. I'm not--
I'm not thinking about her.

72
00:04:32.897 --> 00:04:34.315
-It's okay if you are.
-I'm not.

73
00:04:35.108 --> 00:04:36.234
I haven't for months now.

74
00:04:36.943 --> 00:04:37.902
Okay.

75
00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:41.614
And there's not gonna be a trial.
her folks are gonna settle.

76
00:04:41.698 --> 00:04:45.535
Bryce'll get away with it.
and you know. fuck it all.

77
00:04:45.952 --> 00:04:46.869
Fuck the world.

78
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:50.915
All I care about is you.

79
00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:01.175
Maybe we try to convince ourselves
we're over it.

80
00:05:02.885 --> 00:05:04.220
Maybe it works for a while.

81
00:05:05.805 --> 00:05:06.931
Sure you're ready for this?

82
00:05:07.765 --> 00:05:10.768
Are you sure you are? I've done it before.

83
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:12.353
Yeah. I'm ready. I mean...

84
00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:16.858
I have been. and I am today. Ready.

85
00:05:17.191 --> 00:05:18.526
-Okay.
-Yeah.

86
00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:30.705
-Is this okay?
-Yes.

87
00:05:38.921 --> 00:05:41.507
-What is that?
-It's nothing.

88
00:05:42.133 --> 00:05:44.052
-Keep going.
-Wait. those are cuts.

89
00:05:45.720 --> 00:05:48.014
-You cut down there?
-I used to. a long time ago.

90
00:05:48.097 --> 00:05:49.307
But those are recent.

91
00:05:51.142 --> 00:05:54.979
You're supposed to call me
if you even just think about it.

92
00:05:55.063 --> 00:05:57.148
Where are your rubber bands?
Have you been trying meditation?

93
00:05:57.398 --> 00:06:00.151
Meditation is the most fucking
boring thing in the world.

94
00:06:01.110 --> 00:06:03.029
Then we're going to take
a mindfulness walk.

95
00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:05.990
I'm fucking serious. Skye.

96
00:06:07.283 --> 00:06:09.744
I will do whatever I have to do.
I will text you every hour.

97
00:06:09.827 --> 00:06:12.705
Okay. Okay. I'm sorry.

98
00:06:14.749 --> 00:06:15.792
I promise I'll call.

99
00:06:17.877 --> 00:06:18.711
Okay.

100
00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:24.050
I tried not thinking about it.

101
00:06:24.592 --> 00:06:27.887
Some days I was able to shut it all out
and live my life.

102
00:06:28.721 --> 00:06:30.014
Some days I wasn't.

103
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:39.941
But then I got home last night
and got news I wasn't expecting.

104
00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:49.158
- How's Skye?
- She's good.

105
00:06:50.034 --> 00:06:51.327
You should invite her in.

106
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:54.122
We haven't seen her since.
what. the seventh grade?

107
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:58.126
-She hasn't really changed.
-We'll have her over for dinner.

108
00:06:59.377 --> 00:07:03.548
-Um. Skye doesn't really do dinner.
-She doesn't eat?

109
00:07:04.173 --> 00:07:07.677
I mean. no. she eats.
just not in situations with parents.

110
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.638
Clay. I need to talk to you
about the trial.

111
00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:15.309
What? What trial?

112
00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:18.563
Hannah's trial. It's moving forward.

113
00:07:18.896 --> 00:07:19.814
What?

114
00:07:21.691 --> 00:07:24.444
-You told me it was settled.
-We thought it was.

115
00:07:24.819 --> 00:07:27.989
But the Bakers rejected
the district's final offer today.

116
00:07:28.739 --> 00:07:29.699
It starts tomorrow.

117
00:07:31.826 --> 00:07:34.912
Tomorrow? How is that possible?

118
00:07:37.081 --> 00:07:38.875
They were up against the trial date.

119
00:07:38.958 --> 00:07:41.252
At the last minute.
the Bakers rejected the settlement.

120
00:07:43.921 --> 00:07:46.007
So. I'll get to testify about Bryce?

121
00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:50.094
Sonya did tell me
that you're not on either witness list.

122
00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:52.388
Why not?

123
00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:55.808
Clay. each side chooses witnesses
based on a variety of factors.

124
00:07:56.058 --> 00:07:57.351
Bryce raped Hannah.

125
00:07:58.186 --> 00:08:00.605
Why is nobody talking about that?
You heard his confession.

126
00:08:00.688 --> 00:08:02.690
You heard everything.
before you dropped out.

127
00:08:02.940 --> 00:08:04.233
I didn't drop out of the case.

128
00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:07.945
I withdrew because your involvement
created a conflict of interest.

129
00:08:08.029 --> 00:08:10.531
Well. I'm not involved anymore.
so can someone do something?

130
00:08:10.823 --> 00:08:12.366
If we knew the girl on tape nine.

131
00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:14.368
Mom. it's not my place to tell you that.

132
00:08:14.452 --> 00:08:19.040
-If she would come forward--
-This is a fucking joke. He confessed!

133
00:08:19.123 --> 00:08:21.042
Clay. I'm worried about your anger.

134
00:08:23.002 --> 00:08:26.506
You're worried about my anger?
That's what you're worried about?

135
00:08:29.926 --> 00:08:31.594
I'm not angry. Mom. I'm fine.

136
00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:34.222
That's why you're never home?

137
00:08:35.556 --> 00:08:36.390
We had a deal.

138
00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:40.978
I've had perfect attendance. kept up
my grades. I get to have a life of my own.

139
00:08:41.062 --> 00:08:45.066
The deal was that you would be safe.
You put a lock on your door.

140
00:08:45.149 --> 00:08:47.276
Which you found out by trying to open it?

141
00:08:49.737 --> 00:08:52.156
Clay. I know this is going to be
very hard for you.

142
00:08:52.782 --> 00:08:53.616
It's not.

143
00:08:55.117 --> 00:08:58.871
I haven't thought about Hannah in months.
So I'll just keep on like that.

144
00:09:33.447 --> 00:09:35.157
This trial going forward.

145
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:37.410
it affects the whole town.

146
00:09:38.077 --> 00:09:39.870
We have to think about it all over again.

147
00:09:39.954 --> 00:09:41.956
how Hannah lived and how she died.

148
00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:47.336
And how it changed all our lives.

149
00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:04.562
-Hey. buddy.
-Hey. Dad.

150
00:10:04.645 --> 00:10:09.150
So. your mom isn't too happy
about you going back to school tomorrow.

151
00:10:09.233 --> 00:10:11.152
Well. I have to go back with Jessica.

152
00:10:11.986 --> 00:10:14.947
We promised we'd go back together.
and she's going back tomorrow.

153
00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:17.950
Okay. but we were thinking
more like a week. maybe two?

154
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:19.619
Dad. it has to be now.

155
00:10:19.869 --> 00:10:22.163
- 'Cause of the trial?
- Yeah.

156
00:10:22.246 --> 00:10:25.791
And I know people have been
talking about me for months now.

157
00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:27.960
-Who's been talking?
-It's a small town. Dad.

158
00:10:28.961 --> 00:10:31.297
I can't even go outside
without people looking at me.

159
00:10:31.547 --> 00:10:33.132
Or talking about what I did.

160
00:10:33.966 --> 00:10:37.762
Or what Hannah did and I failed to do.
And I'm sick of hiding from them all.

161
00:10:37.845 --> 00:10:40.723
You're not hiding from anyone.
You're recuperating.

162
00:10:40.806 --> 00:10:43.309
I can still do that. Just out there.

163
00:10:44.143 --> 00:10:47.188
And Hannah's trial means
people are finally gonna hear her story.

164
00:10:47.271 --> 00:10:48.689
and I want to help tell it.

165
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:51.400
Okay. Well. you keep pushing ahead.

166
00:10:52.443 --> 00:10:55.154
I'll tell the boss lady
you're feeling stronger.

167
00:10:56.781 --> 00:10:58.032
Good work today. by the way.

168
00:10:59.617 --> 00:11:01.202
You think I'll get to testify?

169
00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:05.998
I don't know. I think that's up
to your doctors and the court.

170
00:11:06.791 --> 00:11:07.917
Okay? Get some sleep.

171
00:11:09.210 --> 00:11:10.044
I love you.

172
00:11:22.598 --> 00:11:24.058
Hey. what'd they say?

173
00:11:25.142 --> 00:11:29.480
-I can go. How about you?
-They don't like it. but they said yes.

174
00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:31.399
This trial has me freaked out.

175
00:11:33.442 --> 00:11:36.529
What have people been saying about us?
What do they know?

176
00:11:37.363 --> 00:11:38.614
We're gonna find out.

177
00:11:39.949 --> 00:11:40.783
Jess...

178
00:11:40.991 --> 00:11:43.494
Look. whatever happens.
we're gonna stick to the plan.

179
00:11:43.828 --> 00:11:45.121
I don't remember what happened to me.

180
00:11:45.204 --> 00:11:47.206
just like you don't remember
what happened to you.

181
00:11:47.665 --> 00:11:49.250
-Right?
-Right.

182
00:11:51.293 --> 00:11:53.212
You feel okay about seeing Bryce again?

183
00:11:57.174 --> 00:11:59.093
Yeah. Totally.

184
00:12:15.234 --> 00:12:16.152
You hurt.

185
00:12:17.528 --> 00:12:20.614
Worse. you feel... powerless.

186
00:12:32.793 --> 00:12:35.421
I know some people don't want us
to talk about what happened...

187
00:12:41.093 --> 00:12:43.804
but if we don't talk about it.
it's never going to change.

188
00:12:48.893 --> 00:12:51.770
So it's important for everyone
to understand how it all happened.

189
00:12:52.855 --> 00:12:54.440
The whole story. you know?

190
00:13:11.457 --> 00:13:14.001
Because things at Liberty
are as bad as they've ever been.

191
00:13:14.335 --> 00:13:15.669
Mom. it's gonna be fine.

192
00:13:16.545 --> 00:13:19.757
No. I don't mind being the first kid
to testify. I want to be the first.

193
00:13:23.344 --> 00:13:25.763
Yeah. I told the lawyers that. I know.

194
00:13:27.056 --> 00:13:27.890
Yeah. I know.

195
00:13:30.893 --> 00:13:33.729
All right. look.
I'll be home soon. Okay? Bye.

196
00:13:35.397 --> 00:13:37.149
And I don't want to be afraid anymore.

197
00:13:48.077 --> 00:13:49.620
I don't want to be afraid.

198
00:13:52.957 --> 00:13:55.209
I don't know why this case
is going forward.

199
00:13:55.292 --> 00:13:57.169
I don't why you need to be the first.

200
00:13:57.920 --> 00:14:00.714
-The way these kids abuse you--
-That's why I have to be first.

201
00:14:02.007 --> 00:14:04.552
They want me to talk
about how things are at school.

202
00:14:05.719 --> 00:14:07.179
and somebody has to do that.

203
00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:10.099
It's very brave of you. Tyler.
to want to do this for Hannah.

204
00:14:10.182 --> 00:14:12.184
It's not just for Hannah. okay?

205
00:14:12.268 --> 00:14:15.729
It's for me. and Alex. and...

206
00:14:18.691 --> 00:14:19.900
and I have to.

207
00:14:21.402 --> 00:14:24.822
Okay. your dad's on a double and they have
extra units outside the courthouse.

208
00:14:24.905 --> 00:14:28.617
If you need anything. call me. okay?
I can get coverage if I have to.

209
00:14:31.954 --> 00:14:33.706
Mom. did I leave a note?

210
00:14:37.084 --> 00:14:39.336
Yes. You left a note.

211
00:14:40.004 --> 00:14:41.171
I want to see it.

212
00:14:41.255 --> 00:14:44.383
Alex. honey. I--
I don't know that you're ready to--

213
00:14:44.466 --> 00:14:46.802
What? To know the truth?
Or know why I did it?

214
00:14:49.263 --> 00:14:51.307
Is this that you don't want me
to think about it

215
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:53.601
or you just don't want to talk about it?

216
00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:58.188
It's my goddamn note. Mom.
I want to see it!

217
00:14:58.856 --> 00:15:01.817
-What. did you throw it away?
-Of course we didn't throw it away.

218
00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:07.114
Okay. How about I give it to you
the next time you see Dr. Ellman?

219
00:15:07.406 --> 00:15:12.703
God. Mom. I promise you.
I'll talk to him about it. Please.

220
00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:35.768
Do you want to talk about it?

221
00:15:40.522 --> 00:15:42.733
Um...

222
00:15:45.027 --> 00:15:46.111
What does this mean?

223
00:15:46.528 --> 00:15:48.948
"I could have stopped it."
What does that mean?

224
00:15:49.615 --> 00:15:51.200
How could I have stopped it?

225
00:15:51.659 --> 00:15:54.328
It just means
that you felt terrible guilt.

226
00:15:54.870 --> 00:15:59.583
That you felt responsible. but that
is too much for any one person to take on.

227
00:15:59.667 --> 00:16:01.168
You know that now. right?

228
00:16:04.088 --> 00:16:05.422
"I could have stopped it."

229
00:16:08.676 --> 00:16:09.677
Good morning.

230
00:16:11.345 --> 00:16:13.055
Are you ready for battle?

231
00:16:14.181 --> 00:16:17.142
Is anyone ever really ready
for something like this?

232
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:19.687
You are. We are.

233
00:16:23.857 --> 00:16:28.696
Thank you. Jackie. for being here.
Truly. it's above and beyond.

234
00:16:28.779 --> 00:16:29.822
This is what I do.

235
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:34.326
I'll be the only one in that room
who truly knows what you're going through.

236
00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:37.830
Remember that. I will be your strength.

237
00:16:38.831 --> 00:16:41.291
I'm not afraid. I'm not.

238
00:16:41.375 --> 00:16:46.130
I mean. for so long. I've...
I've dreaded this day. but now I'm just...

239
00:16:47.631 --> 00:16:48.966
-I'm angry.
-Mm-hm.

240
00:16:49.883 --> 00:16:52.845
-I'm angry. At everyone.
-Good.

241
00:16:53.137 --> 00:16:54.138
Hold on to that.

242
00:16:55.305 --> 00:16:57.641
And your husband.
were you able to convince him to--?

243
00:16:58.892 --> 00:16:59.727
No.

244
00:17:05.065 --> 00:17:07.317
Part of me didn't want
to come to court today.

245
00:17:09.236 --> 00:17:10.487
But I knew I had to be here.

246
00:17:12.281 --> 00:17:13.157
For Hannah.

247
00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:14.867
For her mom.

248
